wsdl:operation.name: AddAttachment
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Attach a file to a WebEOC board entry.

wsdl:operation.name: GetPositions
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Get a list of the WebEOC positions. Administrator access required

wsdl:operation.name: GetUsersByPosition
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Get a list of the WebEOC users that belong to specific position. Administrator access required. Raises an exception if the positions does not exist.

wsdl:operation.name: GetPositionsForUser
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Get the list of positions that a user can fill. Administrator access required.

wsdl:operation.name: AddUser
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Add a user to the database. Administrator access required. An exception will be raised if a user already exists with the same username. If a color value is supplied, an exception will be raised if the value is not a valid color string(6 digit hexadecimal string)

wsdl:operation.name: AddUserToPosition
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Add a user to a position assignment. Administrator access required. An exception will be raised if the user or position does not exist

wsdl:operation.name: RemoveUserFromPosition
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Remove a user from a position assignment. Administrator access required. An exception will be raised if the user or position does not exist

wsdl:operation.name: DeleteUserIfNoPositions
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Delete a user from WebEOC. Administrator access required. An exception will be raised if the user does not exist or if the user is the same user supplied in the credentials. Returns false if the user was unable to be deleted due to position member. Returns true if the user was deleted

wsdl:operation.name: DeleteUser
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Delete a user from WebEOC. Administrator access required. An exception will be raised if the user does not exist or if the user is the same user supplied in the credentials or if the user is not deleteable (WebEOC Administrator)

wsdl:operation.name: GetBoardNames
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Get a list of the WebEOC boards. Administrator access required

wsdl:operation.name: GetInputViews
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Get the list of Input views for a specific board. Administrator access required

wsdl:operation.name: GetDisplayViews
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Get the list of Display views for a specific board. Administrator access required

wsdl:operation.name: GetViewFields
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Get the list of fields for a particular view. Administrator access required.

wsdl:operation.name: AddData
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Add a new entry to a WebEOC board.

wsdl:operation.name: UpdateData
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Update an existing entry in a WebEOC board.

wsdl:operation.name: UpdateDataBatch
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Batch method for adding/updating entires in a WebEOC board.

wsdl:operation.name: GetUpdatedData
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Get the board entries that have been added or updated since UpdatedTime

wsdl:operation.name: GetIncidents
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Get the list of incidents that a specific user has access to.

wsdl:operation.name: AddIncident
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Add an incident to WebEOC

wsdl:operation.name: GetLists
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Get a DataTable of lists. Administrator access required

wsdl:operation.name: GetListItems
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Get a DataTable of items in a WebEOC list. Administrator access required

wsdl:operation.name: GetListItemsByListName
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Get a DataTable of items in a WebEOC list that a specific user has access to. Administrator access required

wsdl:operation.name: SaveList
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Save a WebEOC list. Administrator access required

wsdl:operation.name: DeleteList
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Delete a WebEOC list. Administrator access required

wsdl:operation.name: SaveListItem
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Save a WebEOC list item. Administrator access required

wsdl:operation.name: DeleteListItem
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Delete a WebEOC list item. Administrator access required
